ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Speaking fluently 1 is course in which you can learn some skills to communicate in English, how to be a good participant in class discussion and how to get and summarize information from reading materials. I'll recommend this course to some other foreign students who need to practice their English because although students can also practice English by themselves, teachers may also help them a lot in class.
I definitely will recommend this course to other students, especially to the international students. It is very helpful.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Although the language itself is not related to my major, communication is very important during my research. This course is very helpful because it helped me to enhance the ability to express my ideas properly and fluently both in professional classes and in lab.
I am making progresses on my academic skills which are very crucial to my research and profession.
